It looks like the infamous {{com.ctc.wstx.stax.WstxInputFactory cannot be cast to javax.xml.stream.XMLInputFactory}} exception is happening because TransactionTemplate sets a different classloader.

I found a hacky way around this by manually setting the classloader inside transaction code and setting it back after I'm done calling the problematic API:

{code}
transactionTemplate.execute(new TransactionCallback<Object>() {
            @Override
            public Object doInTransaction() {
                ClassLoader transactionCCL = currentThread.getContextClassLoader();
                System.out.println("current CCL: " + transactionCCL);

                currentThread.setContextClassLoader(origCCL);
                System.out.println(XMLInputFactory.newInstance()); // WORKS NOW!
                currentThread.setContextClassLoader(transactionCCL);

                return null;
            } 
        });
{code}

Is there a better way to do this? Would appreciate any advice here.

